Short for assembly language. Refers to a family of low-level coding languages that use hexedecimal and commands to perform functions. Most useful because the code can refer to directly communicate with the hardware of a computer.
For example, many old computers used 6502ASM as their primary coding language.
Another example is Roller Coaster Tycoon 2, which was written entirely in x86 ASM
Some of the first high-level coding languages that were made to replace this complex kind of coding were Pascal and BASIC.
